  "texts": [
    "A stationary policy π maps each estate to a probability distribution over the action space.",
    "The authors define the value Z π as the sum of discounted rewards along the agent's inter- action with the environment, the value functions as vectors in R S×A, and consider the expected reward function as one of those vectors.",
    "Therefore, they define a Bellman operator τ π and an optimality operator τ like in Eqs.",
    "21 and 22, where P is the transition function (as defined in Sect. 2).",
    "Instead of expectation, they consider the full distribution of the variable Z π, which they call value distribution."
  ],
